column6: This is electrically neutral in CHEBI but in COB it is generic. We should make it union of molecule and polyatomic ion
we think our uncharged atom is actually chebi:atom, to be discussed with CHEBI people
follow up with CHEBI on nomenclature
we are not sure if these are equivalent, or if we even want to retain this. Follow up with Colin
we currently use a different text definition but we believe they do not contradict
These can't be equivalent because COB drug product is a material entity, and ChEBI's drug is a role. See issue #140 for more information.

The ChEBI notion of a role doesn't strictly follow the BFO sense of either being a role or disposition, meaning that it's hard, if not impossible, to impose BFO order to this branch of ChEBI. See issue #173
may be revised to be narrower
There is no inverse for 'executes' STATO, only in COB.
In RO, 'inheres in' is the inverse of 'bearer of'.
There is no inverse for 'is about' in IAO.
